{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1a56d329-d5d8-4f64-a1f0-c405742bc059","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example usage:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod, Ignore(\"Waiting on bug fix #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Waiting on bug fix #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test, Ignore(\"Waiting on bug fix #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test, Skip(\"Waiting on bug fix #123\")]\npublic async Task MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as **skipped/ignored** (not failed) in test results, with your reason visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"21b9cf2e-603f-45ca-b053-bc5f7517006f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":305,"requestId":"67C9:1FC0A0:161E103:18E96AC:69FD3A12"},"id":"a4012208-3253-45c5-8683-ab1ec8591e0d","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:19:21.068Z","parentId":"5b6c79e8-3047-4627-a939-255bfb6cfa9b"}
